    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Phragmatopoma sp. A, Complete body, dorsal view. B, Opercular crown, up view. C, Median ridge. D, Operculum, lateral view. E, Outer paleae. F, Middle paleae. G, Inner paleae. H, Verticillate abdominal chaetae. I, Abdominal uncini. Scale bars: A: 2 mm; B: 500 μm; C: 300 μm; D: 1 mm; E, H: 50 μm; F: 150 μm; G: 100 μm; I: 10 μm. Abbreviation: op, outer paleae; mp, middle paleae; ip, inner paleae; mr, median ridge; pl, median plume; lt, lateral teeth." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4406656/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

